cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.PF 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with the modeling and analysis of heterogeneous cellular networks. It may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it involves the analysis of signal-to-interference-plus-noise ratio (SINR) and the probability of coverage/outage. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as cellular networks are a type of social network. It may also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) as the paper discusses the average rate achieved by a mobile user. Finally, it could be classified under cs.PF (Performance) as the paper analyzes the average load on each tier of BSs.
